******
[1] Japan
Date: Sun 6 Apr 2014
Source: The Star, Bloomberg report [edited]
http://www.thestar.com/news/world/2014/04/06/disease_puts_a_pox_on_plum_blossom_season_in_tokyo.html


Famed Plum Park will cut down its trees
---------------------------------------
A Tokyo park once named Japan's best for viewing plum blossoms is cutting down all its trees after losing a 5-year battle with plum pox. Umeno Koen in western Tokyo's Ome City closed after its annual plum blossom festival.

The park's remaining 1266 trees will be felled after the clearing of some 2600 others failed to contain a 2009 outbreak of the disease [see ProMED-mail post 20100424.1317]. Ome plans to wait until the area has been free of plum pox for 3 years before replanting.

The discovery of the virus in Umeno Koen was the 1st instance of the disease in Japan, according to Ome City.

